cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper discusses the use of adversarial image perturbations (AIP) for privacy protection, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a game theoretical framework for studying the interaction between users and recognition systems, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of person recognition techniques, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
